Dialogue: 2,0:00:03.05,0:00:04.39,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,别骑骆驼了
Dialogue: 1,0:00:03.05,0:00:04.39,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Forget camels. 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:04.39,0:00:09.19,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,想象一下，驾驭着一台90英尺长的巨兽巴士
Dialogue: 1,0:00:04.39,0:00:09.19,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Imagine cruising through the Sahara in a 90-foot long monster bus 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:09.19,0:00:11.90,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,驰骋撒哈拉，那轮子比大老爷们还高
Dialogue: 1,0:00:09.19,0:00:11.90,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,with wheels taller than a grown man. 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:11.90,0:00:16.31,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不仅有豪华餐厅，邮轮般的舷窗
Dialogue: 1,0:00:11.90,0:00:16.31,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Complete with lounges for fine dining, portholes like an ocean liner, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:16.31,0:00:21.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,更有碾碎沙丘、开辟坦途的强劲马力
Dialogue: 1,0:00:16.31,0:00:21.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and enough horsepower to crush dunes in two highways. 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:21.02,0:00:24.69,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,1932年，真有人动手造了这玩意儿
Dialogue: 1,0:00:21.02,0:00:24.69,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,In 1932, someone actually tried to build this. 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:24.69,0:00:27.69,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,堪称世上最离谱的陆地巡洋舰
Dialogue: 1,0:00:24.69,0:00:27.69,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The world's most ridiculous land yacht. 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:27.69,0:00:31.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,后来呢？它又为何会湮没于黄沙之中？
Dialogue: 1,0:00:27.69,0:00:31.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,What happened? And why did it vanish into the sand?
Dialogue: 2,0:00:37.90,0:00:44.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,百年以来，火车曾是陆地霸主，以速度、舒适和奢华穿梭于列国之间
Dialogue: 1,0:00:37.90,0:00:44.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,For a hundred years, trains ruled the land, crossing nations in speed, comfort, and luxury. 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:44.07,0:00:46.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但火车离不开铁轨
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.07,0:00:46.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But trains need railway tracks. 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:46.65,0:00:50.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,随着汽车的崛起，工程师们萌生了一个新点子
Dialogue: 1,0:00:46.65,0:00:50.10,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And with the rise of the motor car, engineers had a new idea. 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:50.10,0:00:53.04,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,要是能把铁路开进蛮荒之地呢
Dialogue: 1,0:00:50.10,0:00:53.04,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,What if you could bring the railway to the wild? 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:53.04,0:00:57.47,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,既然汽车取代了马匹，那现在，也该轮到骆驼下岗了
Dialogue: 1,0:00:53.04,0:00:57.47,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And just as the car had replaced the horse, now it was the camel's turn. 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:57.47,0:01:01.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们管这叫“新沙漠之舟”
Dialogue: 1,0:00:57.47,0:01:01.74,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And they called this idea the New Ship of the Desert.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:01.74,0:01:04.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这个雄心勃勃的设计长86英尺
Dialogue: 1,0:01:01.74,0:01:04.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This was ambitiously designed to be 86 feet long, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:04.92,0:01:08.28,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,高耸于沙漠26英尺之上
Dialogue: 1,0:01:04.92,0:01:08.28,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,operate at 26 feet high above the desert sands, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:08.28,0:01:13.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,由两台900马力的迈巴赫引擎驱动
Dialogue: 1,0:01:08.28,0:01:13.08,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and be propelled by twin Maybach engines, each with 900 horsepower, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.08,0:01:16.86,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,能拉动超过20吨的货物
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.08,0:01:16.86,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,able to carry more than 20 tons of freight.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:16.86,0:01:19.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,再聊聊那些巨轮
Dialogue: 1,0:01:16.86,0:01:19.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And let's talk about those giant wheels. 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:19.12,0:01:25.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,构想是，整个沙漠之舟的车身悬于液压弹簧的摇篮上
Dialogue: 1,0:01:19.12,0:01:25.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The idea was that the entire body of the desert ship would be suspended in a cradle of hydraulic springs, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:25.65,0:01:31.04,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,靠着直径15英尺的巨轮翻越沙丘
Dialogue: 1,0:01:25.65,0:01:31.04,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,with the giant wheels, 15 feet in diameter, carrying it over the dunes.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:31.77,0:01:33.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,由于这玩意的惊人重量
Dialogue: 1,0:01:31.77,0:01:33.77,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And because of the sheer weight of the craft, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:33.77,0:01:39.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,轮子基本就充当了巨型压路机，在身后压出一条路来
Dialogue: 1,0:01:33.77,0:01:39.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the wheels would essentially be acting like giant steamrollers, and creating a road behind them.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:39.92,0:01:43.95,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这片被压实的沙地将为当地人
Dialogue: 1,0:01:39.92,0:01:43.95,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This packed and crushed sand would facilitate travel for the locals, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:43.95,0:01:46.57,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,或是后方的其他车辆提供便利
Dialogue: 1,0:01:43.95,0:01:46.57,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,or any other vehicles following behind. 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:46.57,0:01:48.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,脑补一下某种护航队
Dialogue: 1,0:01:46.57,0:01:48.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Imagine some sort of convoy.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:48.67,0:01:51.33,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But let's just pause for a second and talk about the physics.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:48.71,0:01:51.33,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但咱们先打住，聊聊物理学
Dialogue: 2,0:01:51.33,0:01:55.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因为这想法固然疯狂，也不乏可取之处
Dialogue: 1,0:01:51.33,0:01:55.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Because whilst the idea was insane, and with merit, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:55.02,0:01:57.17,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但沙漠可不是善茬
Dialogue: 1,0:01:55.02,0:01:57.17,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the desert is not forgiving.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:57.17,0:01:59.79,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这台机器能驾驭地形没错
Dialogue: 1,0:01:57.17,0:01:59.79,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This machine could handle the terrain. 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:59.79,0:02:02.95,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,问题是，地形驾驭不了它
Dialogue: 1,0:01:59.79,0:02:02.95,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The problem is, the terrain couldn't handle it.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:02.95,0:02:05.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,沙子不会被压实变成沥青
Dialogue: 1,0:02:02.95,0:02:05.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Sand doesn't compress and become asphalt. 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:05.80,0:02:07.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它只会位移
Dialogue: 1,0:02:05.80,0:02:07.10,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It shifts.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:07.10,0:02:10.81,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,宽轮子是管用，但它们依旧沉重且集中
Dialogue: 1,0:02:07.10,0:02:10.81,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Wide wheels help, but they're still heavy and concentrated.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:10.81,0:02:14.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,迈巴赫驱动的坦克可不轻巧
Dialogue: 1,0:02:10.81,0:02:14.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,A Maybach-powered tank is not light on its feet, 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:14.22,0:02:16.84,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,液压悬挂听着很未来
Dialogue: 1,0:02:14.22,0:02:16.84,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and hydraulic suspension sounds futuristic, 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.84,0:02:21.15,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但你想象一下1932年在沙尘暴里修它
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.84,0:02:21.15,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,but imagine trying to service that in a sandstorm in 1932.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:21.15,0:02:26.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但工程师们相信，只要燃料管够
Dialogue: 1,0:02:21.15,0:02:26.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But the engineers believed that it would be able to move it around 30 miles per hour over the sand dunes, 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:26.22,0:02:30.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它能在沙丘上以每小时30英里的速度跑出6000英里的续航
Dialogue: 1,0:02:26.22,0:02:30.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,with a range of about 6,000 miles with adequate fuel on board.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:30.72,0:02:36.39,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这确实很牛了，毕竟普通汽车可跑不了6000英里
Dialogue: 1,0:02:30.72,0:02:36.39,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Which is very impressive indeed, considering normal cars can't do 6,000 miles.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:36.39,0:02:42.26,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,或者说牛大了，我必须提醒你，撒哈拉沙漠从南到北也就18000英里
Dialogue: 1,0:02:36.39,0:02:42.26,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This is so impressive, that I have to remind you that the Sahara is only 18,000 miles top to bottom.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:42.26,0:02:45.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,所以，这玩意的实际续航，你懂的
Dialogue: 1,0:02:42.26,0:02:45.32,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,So, real range may vary of this actual craft.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:45.32,0:02:50.30,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,至于短途旅行，我稍后会讲它们有多逆天
Dialogue: 1,0:02:45.32,0:02:50.30,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,For shorter trips, and I'll get into the details of how crazy they were later, 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:50.30,0:02:52.97,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,速度和续航大概都只有一半
Dialogue: 1,0:02:50.30,0:02:52.97,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the speed and range was about half.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:52.97,0:02:54.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,要控制这么个大家伙
Dialogue: 1,0:02:52.97,0:02:54.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,To control such a large beast, 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:54.92,0:03:01.37,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,还得有第三台小点的，7.5升的柴油引擎来为船上所有的电子设备供电
Dialogue: 1,0:02:54.92,0:03:01.37,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,there would be a third, smaller, 7.5 litre diesel engine that would power all of the electronics on board,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.37,0:03:04.76,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,包括用于转向的液压马达
Dialogue: 1,0:03:01.37,0:03:04.76,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,including the hydraulic motor for steering.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:04.76,0:03:09.13,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,船上还会有一台大功率无线电台，用于穿越沙漠时通讯
Dialogue: 1,0:03:04.76,0:03:09.13,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And there would also be a large, powerful radio to communicate across the desert, 
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.13,0:03:12.63,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,以及接收天气预报，跟真的轮船一样
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.13,0:03:12.63,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and to receive weather reports, just like a real ship.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:12.63,0:03:15.82,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当然，这艘船还得依靠技艺高超的领航员观测星象
Dialogue: 1,0:03:12.63,0:03:15.82,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Although, the vessel would rely on skilled navigators 
Dialogue: 2,0:03:15.82,0:03:21.39,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,确保他们不会在瞬息万变的沙丘中迷失方向
Dialogue: 1,0:03:15.82,0:03:21.39,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,to read the stars to make sure that they didn't get lost in the ever-changing sand dunes.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:21.39,0:03:27.42,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不过我猜你一定好奇，在船上旅行究竟是种什么体验
Dialogue: 1,0:03:21.39,0:03:27.42,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But of course, I bet you're wondering, what exactly would it be like to travel on board?
Dialogue: 2,0:03:28.37,0:03:30.61,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,泥嚎，我是Found and Explained的Nick
Dialogue: 1,0:03:28.37,0:03:30.61,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Hello, Nick from Found and Explained here. 
Dialogue: 2,0:03:30.61,0:03:34.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们已经见识过把船开到沙漠中心的后果了
Dialogue: 1,0:03:30.61,0:03:34.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,We've seen what happens when you try to put a ship in the middle of the desert.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:34.54,0:03:37.86,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这么说吧，后勤急得直骂娘
Dialogue: 1,0:03:34.54,0:03:37.86,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Let's just say, logistics can get complicated. 
Dialogue: 2,0:03:37.86,0:03:40.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,沙子无孔不入，骆驼会偷吃你的罐装猪油
Dialogue: 1,0:03:37.86,0:03:40.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Sand gets everywhere, camels get into your canned lard, 
Dialogue: 2,0:03:40.80,0:03:44.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,还有那高温，哎呦我，烤箱都跟冰柜似的
Dialogue: 1,0:03:40.80,0:03:44.70,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and the heat, boy, it makes an oven seem like an icebox.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:44.70,0:03:47.64,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,经营生意要是没趁手的工具，感觉也差不多
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.70,0:03:47.64,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Running a business without the right tools can feel the same. 
Dialogue: 2,0:03:47.64,0:03:51.73,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你手忙脚乱地应付网站、销售、发票、邮件，全在不同的地方
Dialogue: 1,0:03:47.64,0:03:51.73,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,You're juggling websites, sales, invoices, emails, all in different places, 
Dialogue: 2,0:03:51.73,0:03:53.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,指望它们能奇迹般地运转起来
Dialogue: 1,0:03:51.73,0:03:53.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,hoping it somehow floats.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:53.85,0:03:58.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,广告空降5:01
Dialogue: 2,0:05:01.32,0:05:04.20,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因为这艘沙漠之舟实在太高了
Dialogue: 1,0:05:01.32,0:05:04.20,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Because this desert ship was so darn tall, 
Dialogue: 2,0:05:04.20,0:05:08.79,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,乘客的垂直空间相当充裕，足足有三层主甲板
Dialogue: 1,0:05:04.20,0:05:08.79,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,there was actually plenty of vertical space for passengers, with three main decks.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:08.79,0:05:13.46,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,最下层甲板有两个引擎室，一前一后
Dialogue: 1,0:05:08.79,0:05:13.46,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The lowest deck would have twin engine rooms, one at the front and one at the back, 
Dialogue: 2,0:05:13.46,0:05:17.21,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,里面的迈巴赫引擎会像钢铁骆驼般咆哮
Dialogue: 1,0:05:13.46,0:05:17.21,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that would roar like steel camels with those Maybach engines.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:17.21,0:05:19.84,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而十一个可怜的灵魂，也就是船员
Dialogue: 1,0:05:17.21,0:05:19.84,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Whilst eleven poor souls, or crew, 
Dialogue: 2,0:05:19.84,0:05:25.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,生活在它们之间一个摇摇晃晃的金属盒子里，舷窗外只有虚无
Dialogue: 1,0:05:19.84,0:05:25.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,lived in a swaying metal box slung between them, with portholes to nowhere.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:25.22,0:05:30.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,两侧是凹进去的存储区，装着额外的货物
Dialogue: 1,0:05:25.22,0:05:30.25,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,On the sides, there would be concave storage recesses that would contain extra cargo, 
Dialogue: 2,0:05:30.25,0:05:36.69,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,或是一些履带式摩托巴士，用于短途旅行和远足
Dialogue: 1,0:05:30.25,0:05:36.69,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,or the multiple caterpillar motorbuses that would be used for short range trips and excursions.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:36.69,0:05:40.98,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,可惜，关于这些小艇的细节我所知不多
Dialogue: 1,0:05:36.69,0:05:40.98,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, I don't have much in the way of the details of the smaller craft.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:40.98,0:05:45.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我只知道它们有履带，采用了某种半履带设计
Dialogue: 1,0:05:40.98,0:05:45.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,All I know is that they had a caterpillar, and had sort of a half-track design, 
Dialogue: 2,0:05:45.60,0:05:48.44,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,就像我们后来在1940年代看到的那样
Dialogue: 1,0:05:45.60,0:05:48.44,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that we'd see later in the 1940s.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:48.44,0:05:53.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这层甲板上还有通往地面的梯子和升降机
Dialogue: 1,0:05:48.44,0:05:53.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Also on this deck, there would be ladders and lifts to access the ground.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:53.12,0:05:56.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不过我猜，在特定的终点站
Dialogue: 1,0:05:53.12,0:05:56.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Although I imagine, at specific terminals, 
Dialogue: 2,0:05:56.60,0:06:02.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,应该会有个脚手架让乘客进入客舱甲板
Dialogue: 1,0:05:56.60,0:06:02.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,there would be a scaffolding for the passengers to access the actual passenger decks, 
Dialogue: 2,0:06:02.55,0:06:04.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而不是费劲爬上爬下
Dialogue: 1,0:06:02.55,0:06:04.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,rather than climbing up and down.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:04.80,0:06:08.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,第二层是下等客舱
Dialogue: 1,0:06:04.80,0:06:08.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The second level would have a lower-class passenger quarters, 
Dialogue: 2,0:06:08.55,0:06:15.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,毕竟，在900马力隆隆作响的引擎上晃着吊床，这才是奢华旅行的真谛嘛
Dialogue: 1,0:06:08.55,0:06:15.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,because nothing screams luxury travel like swaying hammocks above a rumbling 900-horsepower engine.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:15.07,0:06:18.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,还有雪茄休息室和后部餐厅
Dialogue: 1,0:06:15.07,0:06:18.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,As well as the cigar lounge and the rear dining saloon, 
Dialogue: 2,0:06:18.85,0:06:22.13,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当你在炎热的沙漠中巡航时，那氛围简直绝了
Dialogue: 1,0:06:18.85,0:06:22.13,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which would be a total vibe as you cruise through the hot desert.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.13,0:06:28.84,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这里也有一对凹槽用来放货，主要是食物和水
Dialogue: 1,0:06:22.13,0:06:28.84,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,There would also be a twin set of recesses here for cargo as well, primarily the food and water.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:28.84,0:06:35.03,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不提水也是不行啊，因为这玩意居然还有抽水马桶
Dialogue: 1,0:06:28.84,0:06:35.03,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And yes, I do need to talk about the water, because this thing also had flushable plumbing.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:35.03,0:06:39.53,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,1932年，在沙漠里上厕所
Dialogue: 1,0:06:35.03,0:06:39.53,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,There would be a toilet in the desert in 1932.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:39.53,0:06:43.81,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你就知道他们对这个奢华的理念有多认真了
Dialogue: 1,0:06:39.53,0:06:43.81,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,That's how serious they took the luxury with this idea.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:43.81,0:06:49.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然后在顶层甲板——唯一一个完全不受车轮间隙影响的甲板
Dialogue: 1,0:06:43.81,0:06:49.77,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And then on the top deck, the only one of which was actually free of the wheel clearance,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:49.77,0:06:56.34,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,设有私人的头等客舱，还有一个可以漫步观景的走廊
Dialogue: 1,0:06:49.77,0:06:56.34,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it had the private first-class passenger cabins, and a promenade to stroll around for the views.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:56.34,0:07:00.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这基本上就是个让你在穿越撒哈拉时
Dialogue: 1,0:06:56.34,0:07:00.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Essentially, this was a deck to walk around and contemplate your life choices 
Dialogue: 2,0:07:00.12,0:07:03.81,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在这座巨轮酒店上踱步并思考人生的甲板
Dialogue: 1,0:07:00.12,0:07:03.81,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,as you cross the Sahara in a giant wheeled hotel.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:03.81,0:07:08.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我不知道为什么那时候那么多机器都有长廊，我们在飞艇上也见过
Dialogue: 1,0:07:03.81,0:07:08.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I don't know why so many machines back then had promenades, we saw them in the flying boats,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:08.85,0:07:11.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但我真心希望它们能回归
Dialogue: 1,0:07:08.85,0:07:11.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,but I do wish that they would come back.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:11.54,0:07:16.13,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这些头等舱据说也将是奢华的巅峰
Dialogue: 1,0:07:11.54,0:07:16.13,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,These first-class cabins were also apparently going to be the pinnacle of opulence,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:16.13,0:07:21.76,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,堪比东方快车等著名客运列车，以及，我引用一下
Dialogue: 1,0:07:16.13,0:07:21.76,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,rivaling that of the famous passenger trains like the Orient Express, and I quote,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:21.76,0:07:23.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“最高级的普尔曼车厢”
Dialogue: 1,0:07:21.76,0:07:23.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the finest Pullman cars.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:23.80,0:07:27.86,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而且它会以某种方式人工制冷来对抗太阳的炙烤
Dialogue: 1,0:07:23.80,0:07:27.86,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And it would be somehow artificially cool to combat the sun's rays.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:27.86,0:07:30.31,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,1932年的空调，似乎是吧
Dialogue: 1,0:07:27.86,0:07:30.31,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Aircon in 1932, it seems.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:30.31,0:07:33.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但我稍后会解释这背后的科学道理
Dialogue: 1,0:07:30.31,0:07:33.25,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But I'll explain the science behind that in a moment.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:33.25,0:07:37.24,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在整个船的中间，有一个楼梯间
Dialogue: 1,0:07:33.25,0:07:37.24,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,In the middle of this entire craft, there was a stairwell,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:37.24,0:07:40.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,乘客可以像在游轮上一样爬上甲板
Dialogue: 1,0:07:37.24,0:07:40.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,so passengers could climb the decks like a cruise liner,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:40.54,0:07:46.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,从引擎层一路向上，穿过雪茄休息室，直到星光熠熠的长廊
Dialogue: 1,0:07:40.54,0:07:46.38,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,coming up from the engine level all the way to the cigar lounge to the starlit promenade.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:46.38,0:07:49.24,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然后，为了让它真正成为一艘沙漠之舟
Dialogue: 1,0:07:46.38,0:07:49.24,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Then to really make it a ship of the desert,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:49.24,0:07:54.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在最顶上有一个艉楼甲板，上面有控制室和船长室
Dialogue: 1,0:07:49.24,0:07:54.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,on the very top there was a poop deck that had the control room and the captain's quarters.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:55.31,0:07:58.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在这里，人类历史上最懵圈的11名水手
Dialogue: 1,0:07:55.31,0:07:58.38,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Here, the 11 most confused sailors in human history 
Dialogue: 2,0:07:58.38,0:08:02.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,可以操作这艘船，运载多达56名乘客穿越沙漠
Dialogue: 1,0:07:58.38,0:08:02.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,could operate and transport up to 56 passengers across the desert,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:02.60,0:08:04.39,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不过如果是短途的话
Dialogue: 1,0:08:02.60,0:08:04.39,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,although for shorter distances,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:04.39,0:08:12.93,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这艘陆地之舟也能以不那么精致的奢华，搭载100到300名三等舱乘客
Dialogue: 1,0:08:04.39,0:08:12.93,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it was possible for the land ship to carry over 100 to 300 third-class passengers in less refined luxury.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:13.32,0:08:19.13,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当然，因为这将是一趟时速15英里，穿越沙漠的短途酷热之旅
Dialogue: 1,0:08:13.32,0:08:19.13,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And because this would be a short, hot 15 miles per hour trip over the desert,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:19.13,0:08:24.06,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我猜很多三等舱乘客宁愿选择骑骆驼
Dialogue: 1,0:08:19.13,0:08:24.06,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I imagine many of those third-class passengers would have rather taken the camel instead.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:24.44,0:08:29.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,那么，为什么我们从未见过这艘史诗级的陆地巨舰呢
Dialogue: 1,0:08:24.44,0:08:29.38,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,So why did we never get this epic monster of a land ship?
Dialogue: 2,0:08:33.99,0:08:36.01,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你应该扪心自问的第一个问题是
Dialogue: 1,0:08:33.99,0:08:36.01,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,So the first question you have to ask yourself,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:36.01,0:08:38.46,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这个点子是哪位神人大能想出来的？
Dialogue: 1,0:08:36.01,0:08:38.46,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who was mad enough to dream up all of this?
Dialogue: 2,0:08:38.46,0:08:40.30,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,梦到啥说啥属于是
Dialogue: 1,0:08:38.46,0:08:40.30,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Who wakes up one day and says,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:40.30,0:08:44.14,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“要是东方快车能兼职当个压路机呢？”
Dialogue: 1,0:08:40.30,0:08:44.14,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,what if the Orient Express could moonlight as a steamroller?
Dialogue: 2,0:08:44.14,0:08:48.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,所有鬼点子都少不了魔丸的事，这个也是
Dialogue: 1,0:08:44.14,0:08:48.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Well, behind every mad idea is a mad inventor, and this story was no different.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:48.85,0:08:54.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,来认识一下这位高丸，来自德国的Christian Bischoff Johannes
Dialogue: 1,0:08:48.85,0:08:54.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Meet prolific innovator, Christian Bischoff Johannes from Germany,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.85,0:08:54.12,Yahei-1920x1080,atg3,0,0,0,,高产魔丸
Dialogue: 2,0:08:54.12,0:09:00.53,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他不仅想取代骆驼，还想改变1930年代世界上的许多其他事物
Dialogue: 1,0:08:54.12,0:09:00.53,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who not only wanted to replace the camel, but change a lot of different things in the 1930s world.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:00.53,0:09:04.78,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我现在意识到，说“1930年代想改变世界的德国人”
Dialogue: 1,0:09:00.53,0:09:04.78,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And I now realize saying German who wanted to change the world in the 1930s
Dialogue: 2,0:09:04.78,0:09:10.62,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,可能会让你想到1930年代另一群德国人，也许是某个政治团体
Dialogue: 1,0:09:04.78,0:09:10.62,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,may make you think of a certain other group of German people in perhaps a political group,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:10.62,0:09:14.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我说白了你白说了，还真没纳粹啥事儿
Dialogue: 1,0:09:10.62,0:09:14.77,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,but believe it or not, the Nazis were not involved in this case.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:14.77,0:09:19.47,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这位魔丸在他的职业生涯中，实际上创造了许多发明
Dialogue: 1,0:09:14.77,0:09:19.47,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,A humble innovator would actually go on to create many inventions throughout his career,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:19.47,0:09:24.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,比如一种通用的广告语音设备，本质上是一种交互式听写机
Dialogue: 1,0:09:19.47,0:09:24.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,such as a generic advertising speech device, which was essentially an interactive dictation machine
Dialogue: 2,0:09:24.85,0:09:29.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,可以突出显示价格和促销信息，很像我们今天的电视
Dialogue: 1,0:09:24.85,0:09:29.45,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that would highlight prices and sales, much like the TVs that we have today.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:29.45,0:09:32.35,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但他的另一项发明就很激进了
Dialogue: 1,0:09:29.45,0:09:32.35,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But one of his other inventions was really radical.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:32.35,0:09:34.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,那是一顶能给你降温的帽子
Dialogue: 1,0:09:32.35,0:09:34.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It was a hat that could cool you down.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:34.55,0:09:39.69,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,实际上，这个想法是通过一种轻质的、易挥发的化学物质来冷却身体
Dialogue: 1,0:09:34.55,0:09:39.69,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Actually, it was the idea to cool the body by means of a light, volatile chemical,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:39.69,0:09:41.79,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而非——举例来说——凉风
Dialogue: 1,0:09:39.69,0:09:41.79,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,instead of, say, a cool breeze.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:41.79,0:09:45.31,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,就是说啥呢，你把手腕或头部伸进这个装置
Dialogue: 1,0:09:41.79,0:09:45.31,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The idea was that you would put your wrist or head into this device,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:45.31,0:09:49.75,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,一种特殊的化学物质，由于吸热反应而触感凉爽
Dialogue: 1,0:09:45.31,0:09:49.75,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and a special chemical, which are cool to the touch due to an endothermic reaction,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:49.75,0:09:52.17,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,会冷却你的血液，进而冷却你的全身
Dialogue: 1,0:09:49.75,0:09:52.17,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,would cool your blood and soon your whole body,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:52.17,0:09:55.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但装置的屏障又会防止它造成伤害
Dialogue: 1,0:09:52.17,0:09:55.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,but prevented from causing harm by the barrier of the device. 
Dialogue: 2,0:09:55.67,0:09:56.35,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不赖
Dialogue: 1,0:09:55.67,0:09:56.35,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Neat.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:56.35,0:10:00.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然后他把这个想法应用到了船舱上
Dialogue: 1,0:09:56.35,0:10:00.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,He would then take this idea and apply it to the cabin of a ship,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:00.80,0:10:04.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,再然后他意识到，要是我们把它放到陆地上呢
Dialogue: 1,0:10:00.80,0:10:04.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and then he would realize, what if we put it on land?
Dialogue: 2,0:10:04.52,0:10:08.49,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,于是，这就成了他的毕生杰作，沙漠之舟
Dialogue: 1,0:10:04.52,0:10:08.49,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,So this would become his magnum opus, the ship of the desert.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:08.49,0:10:12.47,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他对这个概念自我感觉相当良好，以至于他费尽心思去申请专利
Dialogue: 1,0:10:08.49,0:10:12.47,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,He was so confident with this concept that he went out of his way to patent it
Dialogue: 2,0:10:12.47,0:10:15.83,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,各个国家各个语言申了个遍
Dialogue: 1,0:10:12.47,0:10:15.83,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,in as many territories and languages as possible.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:15.83,0:10:19.43,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在所有拥有殖民地的国家都申请了专利
Dialogue: 1,0:10:15.83,0:10:19.43,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Patents for all countries with colonial possessions.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:19.43,0:10:22.28,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他还规划了这个概念的最终演变
Dialogue: 1,0:10:19.43,0:10:22.28,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And he planned eventual evolutions of this concept,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:22.28,0:10:26.01,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,比如一个可以在陆地和水上行驶的两栖版本
Dialogue: 1,0:10:22.28,0:10:26.01,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,such as an amphibious version that could travel on both land and water,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:26.01,0:10:30.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而且比较扯的是，他还为它在水下行驶的想法申请了专利
Dialogue: 1,0:10:26.01,0:10:30.70,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and weirdly, also patented the idea for it to travel underwater.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:30.70,0:10:34.04,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,真的，这家伙是奔着把这项目送上月球去的
Dialogue: 1,0:10:30.70,0:10:34.04,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Really, this guy saw this project going to the moon.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:34.04,0:10:39.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,点点关注，揭秘水下陆巡的大结局
Dialogue: 1,0:10:34.04,0:10:39.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And you could subscribe for my eventual video on what happened to underwater land ships.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:39.65,0:10:44.83,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,为了寻找投资者，他真造了个比例模型并花五年时间在世界各地巡回展示 
Dialogue: 1,0:10:39.65,0:10:44.83,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,To seek investors, he actually built a scale model and shopped it around the world for five years
Dialogue: 2,0:10:44.83,0:10:47.27,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,看看有没有冤种接这个项目
Dialogue: 1,0:10:44.83,0:10:47.27,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,to see if anyone was keen to build it.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:47.27,0:10:50.98,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它甚至登上了《现代机械与发明》的封面
Dialogue: 1,0:10:47.27,0:10:50.98,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It even made the cover of modern mechanics and inventions.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:50.98,0:10:53.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它充满了低俗小说的能量
Dialogue: 1,0:10:50.98,0:10:53.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It had pure Pulp Fiction energy, 
Dialogue: 2,0:10:53.02,0:10:55.27,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,有着霓虹绿的油漆、巨大的前灯
Dialogue: 1,0:10:53.02,0:10:55.27,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,with neon green paint, giant headlights,
Dialogue: 2,0:10:55.27,0:10:58.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,还有一个直接从泰坦尼克号上搬来的、带着探照灯的船长塔
Dialogue: 1,0:10:55.27,0:10:58.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and a captain's tower straight off the Titanic with searchlights.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:58.85,0:11:00.66,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这玩意与其说是工程手册
Dialogue: 1,0:10:58.85,0:11:00.66,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It was less engineering manual 
Dialogue: 2,0:11:00.66,0:11:04.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不如说是给那些“喝汽油的纯爷们”看的科幻漫画
Dialogue: 1,0:11:00.66,0:11:04.08,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and more sci-fi comic for the men who drink gasoline.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:04.40,0:11:07.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在大萧条和法西斯主义抬头的背景下
Dialogue: 1,0:11:04.40,0:11:07.45,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And in the midst of the Great Depression and rising fascism,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:07.45,0:11:12.01,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这算得上一个关于进步与和平的梦想，乐观得近乎可笑
Dialogue: 1,0:11:07.45,0:11:12.01,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,this was a dream of progress and peace, almost laughably optimistic.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:12.01,0:11:14.16,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,也许这不仅仅是一辆载具
Dialogue: 1,0:11:12.01,0:11:14.16,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And maybe this wasn't just a vehicle.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:14.16,0:11:18.23,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,也许它是一个象征，象征着殖民野心，象征着不可能的希望
Dialogue: 1,0:11:14.16,0:11:18.23,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Maybe it was a symbol, one of colonial ambition, of impossible hope,
Dialogue: 2,0:11:18.23,0:11:21.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,或者是一个人光荣的、滚滚向前的狂热梦想
Dialogue: 1,0:11:18.23,0:11:21.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,or one man's glorious rolling fever dream.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:21.54,0:11:23.71,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但随着战争的阴云逼近
Dialogue: 1,0:11:21.54,0:11:23.71,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But with war on the horizon, 
Dialogue: 2,0:11:23.71,0:11:29.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,没人有闲工夫琢磨和平、友谊，或者巨型豪华陆地巡洋舰这种蠢点子
Dialogue: 1,0:11:23.71,0:11:29.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,no one had time for silly ideas like peace, friendship, or giant luxury land ships.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:29.65,0:11:33.99,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,就这样，随着世界陷入战争，这个想法也终结了
Dialogue: 1,0:11:29.65,0:11:33.99,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And just like that, the idea ended as the world descended to war.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:33.99,0:11:38.01,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不过我确实好奇，他是否考虑过给它装上几门炮
Dialogue: 1,0:11:33.99,0:11:38.01,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Although I do wonder if he had given any thought to sticking some guns on it.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:38.01,0:11:44.83,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,如果他把它武器化了，德国人在埃及和北非的战斗将会截然不同
Dialogue: 1,0:11:38.01,0:11:44.83,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The battle for Egypt and North Africa for the Germans would have gone very differently indeed, if he had weaponized it.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:44.83,0:11:49.30,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,要不关注一下，未来也许就能看到那个
Dialogue: 1,0:11:44.83,0:11:49.30,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,So maybe subscribe to see that story of the world of giant impossible 
Dialogue: 2,0:11:49.30,0:11:51.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,关于“巨大且虚幻的陆地战舰”的故事了
Dialogue: 1,0:11:49.30,0:11:51.59,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,to build land battleships.
